      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Perhaps you&#8217;ve come to this realization too?</p>
<p>To scale your business much much quicker, you either have to AUTOMATE many of the tasks you do or OUTSOURCE those tasks.</p>
<p>Ideally, you do both &#8211; get it automated AND have an outsourced worker actually do it.</p>
<p>If you make $1.00 / day from a website, you&#8217;ll need 300 similar websites to earn a total of $9000 / month.</p>
<p>But it takes time to build the sites, and the sites then require promotion, and then they have to be updated and upgraded as things change in the industry.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s TOTALLY do-able, and yet incredibly tedious at the same time.</p>
<p>But if you have someone ELSE doing the work &#8211; or even a few people doing the work &#8211; well, you&#8217;re job is just to pull stings and give direction from the top.  And that&#8217;s a LOT more fun, and it takes a lot less time.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s this kind of scaling that put me where I am today, and you&#8217;ve GOT to be outsourcing to scale like this.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve asked John Jonas &#8211; who I LITERALLY learned everything I know about outsourcing from &#8211; to come and give you a talk about outsourcing:</p>
<ul>
<li>How to do it</li>
<li>Where to hire from &#8211; and where to AVOID</li>
<li>What tasks to have your workers do</li>
<li>Cultural differences</li>
<li>Living the 17 Hour Work Week</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="http://www.replacemyself.com/MacPhearson/">Register for the Webinar here</a>, but arrive early too as we&#8217;ll likely run out of room.</p>
