      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><div class="seriesmeta">This entry is part 20 of 23 in the series <a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/series/31-day-internet-marketing-makeover/" title="series-721">31 Day Internet Marketing Makeover</a></div><br /><p>Welcome to Day 20 of the Internet Marketing Makeover (#31DIMM for short)!</p>
<p>Today is a recap day if you’ve not finished any of the past week’s assignments.  If you have, it’s a rest day – enjoy!</p>
<h3>DAY 20 OBJECTIVE</h3>
<p>Catch up on any #31DIMM assignments you’ve not yet finished!</p>
<h3>DAY 20 ASSIGNMENT</h3>
<p>Review the previous Internet Marketing Makeover posts and their tasks and complete anything you haven’t gotten to yet:</p>
<h4><a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/11-resources-for-a-better-looking-website/">11 Resources For a Better Looking Website</a></h4>
<ol>
<li>Update any ugly / old Wordpress themes</li>
<li>Change out header banners</li>
<li>Get an attractive, modern look for your salespages</li>
<li>Add graphical elements with web icons to increase visual interest</li>
</ol>
<h4><a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/generate-link-building-momentum/">Generate Link Building Momentum</a></h4>
<ol>
<li>Determine which social bookmarking process works for you and your business</li>
<li>Implement a daily or weekly bookmarking process</li>
</ol>
<h4><a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/getting-some-background/">Getting Some Background</a></h4>
<ol>
<li>Clean your computer desktop!</li>
</ol>
<h4><a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/earn-more-from-the-same-number-of-visitors/">Earn More From The Same Number of Visitors</a></h4>
<ol>
<li>Determine what questions your market wants the answer to that you can provide as an incentive to sign up for your email list</li>
<li>Determine what format you’ll provide it in (video, audio, email course, PDF, articles on your site, etc.)</li>
<li>Create the incentive piece</li>
</ol>
<h4><a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/turn-your-niche-website-into-a-real-business/">Turn Your Niche Website Into a Real Business</a></h4>
<ol>
<li>Get an autoresponder service</li>
<li>Load your autoresponder with a series of messages</li>
<li>Publish your opt-in form on your website</li>
</ol>
<h4><a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/tracking-optimizing-visitor-profitablity/">Tracking &amp; Optimizing Visitor Profitablity</a></h4>
<ol>
<li>Add a &#8220;Goal&#8221; to your Google Analytics account</li>
<li>Watch for Goal trends in your keyword and referring sites reports</li>
<li>Capitalize on those trends by driving more traffic from sources that convert well</li>
</ol>
