      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><div class="seriesmeta">This entry is part 17 of 23 in the series <a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/series/31-day-internet-marketing-makeover/" title="series-721">31 Day Internet Marketing Makeover</a></div><br /><p>Welcome to Day 17 of the Internet Marketing Makeover (#31DIMM for short)!</p>
<p>Having someone visit your website is a good thing.  Having their email address so you can bring them back to your site over and over, or introduce them to affiliate products, is a GREAT thing.</p>
<p>Too many folks aren&#8217;t capturing emails (particurally in niche markets) and aren&#8217;t maximizing their revenue because of this.</p>
<p>Today you&#8217;ll start squeezing every drop of profit from your website visitors by capturing their email addresses.</p>
<h3>DAY 17 OBJECTIVE</h3>
<p>Design your lead generation funnel.</p>
<h3>DAY 17 ASSIGNMENT</h3>
<p>First and foremost, people need an incentive to sign up for your email list.</p>
<p>(I&#8217;ve done a poor job of it here on this blog&#8230;  You&#8217;ll notice when you visit the site there&#8217;s a slideup ad that tells people to subscribe to get updates when there&#8217;s a new blog post.)</p>
<p>You want to offer folks something they can&#8217;t get unless they subscribe.</p>
<p><a title="Ain't she cute ?" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/37007874@N00/538750839/" target="_blank"><img class="alignright" src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1406/538750839_d4178ba48e_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Ain't she cute ?" /></a>Some classic examples are a 7 day email course or a downloadable PDF course.</p>
<p>At <a href="http://www.30minutebacklinks.com"  class="alinks_links" title="One Way Link Building"  rel="external">30 Minute Backlinks</a>, I offer a &#8220;Free Link Building Tutorial.&#8221;  At <a href="http://www.crowdmountain.com"  class="alinks_links" title="Crowd Mountain"  rel="external">Crowd Mountain</a> I offer a sneak peek video inside the private member&#8217;s area.  On one niche site, I offer a series of messages that help people implement lifestyle changes to help their particular health problem.</p>
<p>Whatever your niche is, people are looking for some kind of answers, and your incentive to join the email list should help them answer those questions.</p>
<p>You can also appeal to curiosity (that&#8217;s what the Crowd Mountain sneak peek video does).</p>
<p>It&#8217;s important that you give them answers in the form of valuable, creative content.  But it&#8217;s also important that you don&#8217;t give away the farm.  If you answer EVERYTHING they want to know, what incentive do they have to buy from you? (Assuming you&#8217;re offering your own or affiliated products for sale).</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re running a site that&#8217;s monetized only by Adsense, you can give people ALL the answers in your course, but with a twist.  Rather than send them an email message with the days&#8217; content inside of it, send them an email message with a link to a page on your site with the day&#8217;s content on it.  That page should also have you Adsense code on it.  This way you&#8217;re bringing them back to your site, to see and possibly click your ads, over and over again.</p>
<p>Today your assignment is to:</p>
<ol>
<li>Determine what questions your market wants the answer to that you can provide as an incentive to sign up for your email list</li>
<li>Determine what format you&#8217;ll provide it in (video, audio, email course, PDF, articles on your site, etc.)</li>
<li>Create the incentive piece</li>
</ol>
<p>Tomorrow we&#8217;ll take your lead generation incentive piece and put it into place &#8211; see you then!</p>
