      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><div class="seriesmeta">This entry is part 16 of 23 in the series <a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/series/31-day-internet-marketing-makeover/" title="series-721">31 Day Internet Marketing Makeover</a></div><br /><p>Welcome to Day 16 of the Internet Marketing Makeover (#31DIMM for short)!</p>
<p>As we&#8217;ve discussed, physical and digital clutter leads to mental clutter, anxiety and underperformance.</p>
<p>In today&#8217;s 31DIMM Assignment, we&#8217;ll remove another aspect of clutter from our digital lives &#8211; the computer desktop!</p>
<h3>DAY 16 OBJECTIVE</h3>
<p>Clean your desktop.</p>
<h3>DAY 16 ASSIGNMENT</h3>
<p>Delete, delete, delete!</p>
<p>That&#8217;s the mantra today!</p>
<p>Most of the files we accumulate on our desktops are shortcuts to programs we didn&#8217;t want shortcuts for in the first place, temporary download files.</p>
<p>Today you&#8217;ll delete all that clutter.</p>
<p>Those files that you do need to keep should be organized according to <a href="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/9-folders/">Day 12&#8217;s 9 Folders</a> principles.</p>
<p>A clean desktop is pure&#8230; zen.</p>
<p>Check mine out after I finished wiping it:</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-916" title="desktop" src="http://www.michellemacphearson.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/desktop.jpg" alt="desktop" width="550" height="345" /></p>
<p><em>(On this Windows machine, I use a little program called <a href="http://www.johnsadventures.com/software/backgroundswitcher/">John&#8217;s Background Switcher</a> to change my desktop background periodically.  Just makes for some fun variety.)</em></p>
<p>Enjoy your minimalist desktop, and check back tomorrow for your next #31DIMM assignment!<em><br />
